                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical"
                android:weightSum="5">

                <com.example.discrollview.MyTextViewHeading
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_weight="1"
                    android:padding="8dp"
                    android:text="EVENT STRUCTURE"
                    android:textAlignment="center"
                    android:textSize="18sp"
                    android:textStyle="bold" />

                <com.example.discrollview.MyTextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_weight="4"
                    android:padding="8dp"
                    android:text="1) The Selected Teams will be first divided into categories based on school level or college level \n \n
2) For each category, teams would be divided into groups and random fixtures will be allotted inside the group such that each team will play more than 1 match \n \n
3) Top 2 teams in each group will be selected for quarterfinals and will have one on one knockout matches. \n \n
4) The team with the lowest win margin would have to face the winner of the school level, and the winners will go to the next level \n \n
5) We will have one on one Knockout matches between the bottom two teams until we have 4 finalists \n \n
6) The top two teams would collide in the 1st Qualifier, the winner directly going to finals, while the loser would be given another chance in the Eliminator by colliding with the winner of the other two teams in the 2nd Qualifier, the winner going to finals. \n \n
7) The loser of the Eliminator would be given the 3rd place \n \n
8) We also have a special prize for the winner of the School level, as a Token of Appreciation." />

            </LinearLayout>

        </android.support.v7.widget.CardView>

